  "summary": "abi-encode ships an encrypted import-time dropper with cron persistence",
  "details": "The package presents itself as an ABI encoder but, on require(), schedules a 42-second setTimeout that AES-256-CBC-decrypts a bundled blob (test/fixtures/keypairs.dat) using a hardcoded key and IV, writes the decoded JavaScript to ~/.cache-db/.node-sync/syncd.js, installs a crontab entry running that file via /usr/bin/node every 12 hours, and spawns it detached with stdio ignored. The payload is delivered as an encrypted file disguised as a test fixture, defeating static inspection. None of this behavior is disclosed in the package's advertised purpose.",
